<br>
Bats and goos drop money.  Spiders drop silk (spiffy Crystalline Silk armor, with tailoring) and those webs with 2 charges of ensnaring roots (mage + root = uber, I've been using them for ulthork emergencies and they rock.  Root, sit, med, make new pet.)<br>
<br>
Goos also drop heads, as has been mentioned.<br>
<br>
Rats are the only things that drop no money or anything of value.<br>
<br>
<br>
Best spot for 34 - 38:<br>
<br>
Go in the caves, first right, down the ladder.  Invis up.  Thru the water, jump over the 3 gaps.  (If you miss a jump just go up the ladder -- jumping is easier because sometimes mobs have the ladder blocked.)<br>
<br>
That room after the last jump / ladder is safe.  Summon your pet, /pet guard here and go to work.  The ones at the ladder will eventually pop up the ladder where you can pull them.  Fire pet (w/ Torch of Alna) rocks down here, just try to avoid letting the mobs run.  Once you have them dead from your spot to the water, it won't even matter if they run.<br>
<br>
Pulls:<br>
2 at the ladder<br>
2 down the first hallway, if you can get them before the dwarf NPC kills them<br>
2 more back the way you came from, near the water<br>
3 down the second hallway<br>
<br>
This is a perfect solo spot.  At 34 you can do most of the pulls, by 38 you'll be doing them all with your more efficient bolts and blazes.  Grouping with 1 other person works, but there's no sense in grouping with more -- you'll run out of mobs.<br>
<br>
<br>
The only time you can have trouble is if you get 2-3 spiders.  You can still take them with a good firepet summons, just keep laying down heals and let the pet's uber FS do the work.  If you lose control, run to where that dwarf is, he'll kill the stuff and then you just go remake your pet and keep going.<br>
<br>
